STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. ROBERT RICHARD HUTCHINSON, Appellant. (No. 41876) 510 P2d 359 Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. Thomas II. Denney, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osbum, Solicitor General, Salem.

Argued May 25,

affirmed May 25, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Fort and Thornton, Judges.
